fields.title: Unidentified Man Spotted Near Hostel Premises
fields.description:
On the night of 12th July 2025, around 11:45 PM, a tall man wearing a black hoodie was seen lurking near the girlsï¿½ hostel boundary wall in the Sector F-8, Islamabad area. He appeared to be circling the premises for almost 20 minutes, repeatedly checking the side gate and looking around suspiciously.
A few hostel residents reported hearing faint knocking on the back windows. The man fled when one of the security guards turned on the searchlight.
The incident has created fear among students, and preventive action is requested.
fields.witnesses: Sana Tariq (Room 203), Maria Khan (Room 205), Guard on duty: Imran (ID #4451)

fields.title: Suspicious Activity Near Meter Box
fields.description: A resident noticed unknown individuals fiddling with the electricity meter installed outside House #119 late at night. Tools were involved, and the box appears tampered with. Since then, the bill has spiked unusually. This may be a case of illegal connections or meter manipulation.
fields.suspect_name: Unknown ï¿½ appeared to be one adult male

fields.title: Open Manhole on Main Road
fields.description: A manhole cover on the main service road has been broken for over a week, creating a dangerous opening. Several bikers have narrowly avoided accidents, and it poses a serious risk to children walking to nearby schools.
fields.location: Main Service Road, near Block D, I-8/4, Islamabad
fields.witnesses: Mr. Danish Irfan (shopkeeper nearby), Ms. Naila Feroze (commuter)

fields.title: Garbage Piled Near School Wall
fields.description: Garbage has been dumped illegally behind the boundary wall of Al-Fajr Public School. The trash pile includes food waste, plastics, and even medical disposables. The foul smell and stray animals pose a health risk to students and staff.
fields.location: Backstreet, near Gate #2, Al-Fajr Public School, G-8/3, Islamabad
fields.suspect_name: Unknown ï¿½ dumping likely done overnight by nearby shopkeepers
fields.witnesses: Mr. Iqbal Shah (school security guard), Ms. Ruqayya Hashmi (biology teacher)
